<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES60-5 - REASSEMBLE - CASE,
        CLUTCH HOUSING AND GEARS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1301201" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="12">
        <title>CASE, CLUTCH HOUSING AND GEARS</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s13012_8.xml" xrefid="f1301209">Figure 9</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk document="s13012_9.xml" xrefid="f1301222">Figure 22</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the countershaft assembly into the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301254">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301254" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301254" filename="../figg13/g1301254.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Countershaft Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the reverse idler gear and thrust washers in the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301255">Figure 55</hotlnk>). Then install the idler shaft with the flat side facing
                the bearing cap.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301255" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301255" filename="../figg13/g1301255.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Install Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the rear countershaft bearing cap, gasket and shims (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301256">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301256" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301256" filename="../figg13/g1301256.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Rear Countershaft Bearing Cap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the lubrication spacer into the countershaft front bearing bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301257">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301257" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301257" filename="../figg13/g1301257.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Lubrication Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the clutch housing and gasket to the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301258">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301258" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301258" filename="../figg13/g1301258.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Clutch Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check countershaft end play (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301259">Figure 59</hotlnk>). It must be set between .001 and .008 inch (.025 and .203
                mm). Adjustments can be made by re-shimming if necessary.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301259" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301259" filename="../figg13/g1301259.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Check Countershaft End Play</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower the mainshaft assembly into the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301260">Figure 60</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301260" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301260" filename="../figg13/g1301260.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Mainshaft Assembly Into Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear bearing cap and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301261">Figure 61</hotlnk>). Remember, mainshaft end play is controlled by the spacer
                and the shims under the loose bearing race in this cap.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301261" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301261" filename="../figg13/g1301261.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Install Rear Bearing Cap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the input pocket bearing with Moly #2 lubricant (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301262">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301262" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301262" filename="../figg13/g1301262.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Lubricate Input Pocket Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the input shaft bearing cap and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301263">Figure 63</hotlnk>). Secure with bolts. Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s13012_33.xml" xrefid="hl1301202">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1301202"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301263" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301263" filename="../figg13/g1301263.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Install Input Shaft Bearing Cap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Stand the transmission upright to check the mainshaft end play (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301264">Figure 64</hotlnk>). First assemble the end fitting and secure it with a
                washer and nut. Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s13012_33.xml" xrefid="hl1301202">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1301202"/>
                </hotlnk>
                . Rotate the mainshaft to properly seat the bearings. Place a dial indicator on the output end of the
                shaft and lift the mainshaft with pry bars. End play must be between .003 and .008 inch (.08 and .20
                mm).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301264" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301264" filename="../figg13/g1301264.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Check Mainshaft End Play</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the transmission back into a horizontal position and place all clutch gears in neutral (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301265">Figure 65</hotlnk>). Install the shift housing and gasket. Secure them with
                bolts. Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s13012_33.xml" xrefid="hl1301202">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1301202"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301265" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301265" filename="../figg13/g1301265.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Install Shift Housing and Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
